gi, F., Regional climate modelling: status and perspectives (2006) J Phys IV, 139, pp. 101-118; Giorgi, F., Mearns, L.O., Introduction to special section: regional climate modelling revisited (1999) J Geophys Res, 104, pp. 6549-6562; Giorgi, F., Bi, X., Pal, J.S., Means, trends and interannual variability in a regional climate change experiment over Europe. Part I: present day climate (1961-1990) (2004) Clim Dyn, 22, pp. 733-756; Giorgi, F., Bi, X., Pal, J.S., Means, trends and interannual variability in a regional climate change experiment over Europe. Part II: future climate scenarios (2071-2100) (2004) Clim Dyn, 23, pp. 839-858; Haylock, M.R., Hofstra, N., Klein Tank, A.M.G., Klok, E.J., Jones, P.D., New, M.A., (2007) European Daily High-resolution Gridded Dataset of Surface Temperature and Precipitation, , http://www.ensembles-eu.org/, Available online from; Hudson, D.A., Jones, R.G., (2002) Simulations of Present-day and Future Climate Over Southern Africa Using HadAM3H, , Hadley Centre Technical Note no 38, Met Office, Exeter, UK; (2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, , IPCC, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press; Jacob, D.A., A note to the simulation of the annual and inter-annual variability of the water budget over the Baltic Sea drainage basin (2001) Meteorol Atmos Phys, 77, pp. 61-73; Jones, P.D., Lister, D.H., The daily temperature record for St. Petersburg (1743-1996) (2002) Clim Change, 53, pp. 253-267; Jones, P.D., Horton, E.B., Folland, C.K., Hulme, M., Parker, D.E., Basnett, T.A., The use of indices to identify changes in climatic extremes (1999) Clim Change, 42, pp. 131-149; Jones, C.G., Ullerstig, A., Willén, U., Hansson, U., The Rossby Centre regional atmospheric climate model (RCA). Part I: model climatology and performance characteristics for present climate over Europe (2004) Ambio, 33, pp. 199-210; Katz, R.W., Brown, B.G., Extreme events in a changing climate: variability is more important than averages (1992) Clim Change, 2